So true. If you're getting frustrated with something it's only going too get worse. Leave your drawing and come back to it with a fresh eye and you should be able to correct a lot of your mistakes. As far as proportions go Just keep on looking at real people. A lot of the time a drawing can look completely wrong becase the weight isn't distributed in the right places. Often Standing figures can look really skewif because in real life that person would be off balance, or it's just that people <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>don't</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> stand like that, regardless of your proporions. This is a very easy mistake to make if you're &quot;constantly using a ruler to figure out if the sizes are right&quot;<br>
